properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 12:03 a.m. CST, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing very strong wind gusts, up to nickel size hail and heavy rain. There are currently two lines of thunderstorms tracking through southern Saskatchewan. One stretches from Fishing Lake to Cupar, and the second stretches from vicinity Last Mountain Lake to east of Val Marie. Both lines of thunderstorms are tracking to the northeast at 20 km/h. Very heavy rainfall in excess of 50 mm per hour is likely with these lines of thunderstorms. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.

properties.Title: Fog Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Near zero visibility in fog is expected or occurring. Early this morning, both Kindersley and North Battleford are reporting significantly reduced visibilities in fog. If travelling in these regions, be prepared for areas of near zero visibility in fog. Fog will lift later this morning. ### Visibility may be significantly and suddenly reduced to near zero. Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of severe thunderstorms that may be capable of producing large hail. Severe thunderstorms are possible this evening. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Locally heavy rain is also possible. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Very strong wind gusts that may cause damage are expected or occurring. In Resolute southeasterly winds will continue to strengthen tonight with gusts of 90 km/h starting overnight tonight. Winds will diminish Friday evening. In Grise Fiord easterly wind gusts are expected to reach, or possibly exceed, 100 km/h. Strong winds are expected to develop overnight and diminish Friday night. ### Damage to buildings, such as to roof shingles and windows, may occur. Loose objects may be tossed by the wind and cause injury or damage. Wind warnings are issued when there is a significant risk of damaging winds. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
